      <scopecontent id="aspace_61465cdd1ec912a022d672bba3a1e01e">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>This collection contains family letters and business papers of James B. Richardson,
            plantation owner and slaveholder, and of his descendants. The letters and papers contain
            references to the allotment of slave labor for road and railroad construction; the
            impressment of slaves for work on fortifications during the Civil War; political
            wrangles; James B. and Richard C. Richardson's activities in the Confederate Army;
            social and economic conditions on South Carolina plantations before, during, and after
            the Civil War; the postwar depression and poverty in the South; and tenant farming
            during the postwar period.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_504113cc4baeb6a92aa8440ef9c7b4e2">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p>The James Burchell Richardson papers were acquired by the David M. Rubenstein Rare Book
            &amp; Manuscript Library in 1939-1940.</p>
      </acqinfo>
